      • toString

        public String toString​()
        Obtains a string representation of the current RationalNumber object.
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        Returns a specific string based on the following rules:
        • Returns NaN if the numerator and denominator of the current object are both 0;
        • Returns PositiveInfinity if the denominator is 0 and the numerator is a positive number;
        • Returns NegativeInfinity if the denominator is 0 and the numerator is a negative number;
        • Returns a string in the format <i>Numerator</i>/<i>Denominator</i>, for example, 3/5, in other circumstances.
        Since:
        1

      • createRationalFromString

        public static RationalNumber createRationalFromString​(String rationalString)
                                               throws NumberFormatException
        Creates a RationalNumber object based on a given string.

        The given string must be in the format <i>Numerator</i>/<i>Denominator</i>, for example, 3/5. To create an object representing an NaN value, pass NaN to this method. To create an object representing a positive infinity value, pass PositiveInfinity. To create an object representing a negative infinity value, pass NegativeInfinity.

        Parameters:
        rationalString - Indicates the string used to create the RationalNumber object.
        Returns:
        Returns the RationalNumber object generated based on the given string.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - Throws this exception if the rationalString is null.
        NumberFormatException - Throws this exception if the rationalString is illegal.
        Since:
        1
